definition: to freeze/to feel very cold/aspic or jelly
Hong Kong, abbr. for 香港[Xiang1 gang3]/surname Gang

sentences.english: Yes, Shanghai is an ice-free port.
sentences.chinese: 是啊，上海港是一個不凍港。

sentences.english: Will Russia have a new ice-free port?
sentences.chinese: 俄羅斯會有一個新的不凍港嗎？

sentences.english: Manufactured goods from Asia keep flowing into this natural ice-free harbor throughout the year.
sentences.chinese: 亞洲的產品一年四季源源不斷地運入這座天然不凍港。

sentences.english: The city and the areas around it are an ice-free port and a nuclear-weapon-free zone.
sentences.chinese: 那城市及其周圍的地方是不凍港和無核區。

sentences.english: This is an ice free harbor.
